b'Since joining Manchester in July 2018, Mahrez has won 2 PL titles, 3 Carabao Cups, 2 Community Shields and 1 FA Cup title. He was one of the most important players for Manchester City last season as he helped his side reach its 1st ever UCL final by scoring in both legs vs PSG. https://t.co/TTo8luWRiz'

b'Born in France, Mahrez made his international debut for\xc2\xa0Algeria\xc2\xa0in 2014. He represented them at the\xc2\xa02014 FIFA World Cup, 2015, 2017 and 2019 African Cup of Nations. In 2016, he was named African Player of the Year and won African Cup of Nations in 2019. https://t.co/PFA8FnI5Ti'

b'Mahrez started his career as a youth player for AAS Sarcelles and turned professional in 2009 with\xc2\xa0Quimper. After 1 season, he moved to\xc2\xa0Le Havre where he spent 3 years. In January 2014, Mahrez signed for\xc2\xa0Leicester City and in 2018, he signed for PL Champions, Manchester City. https://t.co/DjCc3pQOH7'
